result.description:
A presentation of SMART reform proposals:  
a) to promote the market actors’ development-friendly choices, internalising environmental and social externalities in the global supply chains of Products; 
b) to contribute to improved policy coherence between EU development goals and EU non-development policies and regulations impacting on private sector; 
c) to promote changes concerning issues best dealt with on international level, on the Member State level, and by market actors themselves.
